This is a quick synopsis of what is widely agreed upon from both camps.   If you know how to OC a system a p4 1.6a, or 1.8a is the way to go....performance and value since both of those easily OC to 2.4 and 2.5 respectively.  If you don't feel safe OC'ing then go AMD.<br>
<br>
